17/02/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Foreign Minister Kastriot Islami on Monday (16 February) praised the progress achieved in dialogue between Pristina and Belgrade. 
He met with Kosovo Minister of Public Services Jakup Krasniqi to discuss the issue of Kosovo's status and agreed on the importance of transferring UNMIK's competencies to Kosovo authorities.
In other news, Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano met on Monday with Barry Jackson, a senior adviser to US President George W. 
Bush. 
Jackson praised Albania's "great potential" in the fight against terrorism, as well as its participation in the international peacekeeping missions in Iraq and Afghanistan. 
(ATA - 16/02/04)
